<h> offers a wide variety of features for handling screen-displays.

PROMPT 		: used to control your prompt shown
TERMINAL	: used to set terminal type as well as screen-size
BRIEF		: controls text outputting
TOGGLE		: controls certain automatic features (spam, shout, etc)
COMPACT		: eliminates excess whitespace
CLS		: clears your screen and redraws any menu bars
MARGINS		: resets screen boundaries
STATUS BAR      : help file on customizing the status bar
COLOR           : generic information on color
COLOR CODES     : replacement strings for showing color to others

